Interface Dictionary

All Known Implementing Classes:
LPHashtable
public interface Dictionary

ADT for a dictionary type of object. A dictionary contains words and their definitions. A word may have more than one definition. A definition consists of the word type (noun, adjective, verb) and a description.

Version:
23/4/2015
Author:
Stephan Jamieson

Method Summary
 boolean containsWord(String word)
          Returns true if this dictionary contains a definition for the specified word.
 void empty()
          Removes all words from the dictionary.
 List<Definition> getDefinitions(String word)
          Return the entry for the specified word, or null if this dictionary contains no entry for the word.
 void insert(String word, Definition definition)
          Inserts the given word and definition.
 boolean isEmpty()
          Returns true if this dictionary contains no words.
 int size()
          Returns the number of words in this dictionary.
